snippet.textDisplay: Billie Eilish is the thing I get the least and I’m 23. Frankly, I think the thing that I get the least is what it has to do with or how it overlaps with alternative culture or why most sources that I see cover it or want to talk about it really do so. I don’t think I’m trying to not see the appeal or overtly wanting to deliberately dislike it either, but I don’t see the quality of songs or knockout moments or pop being done to such a high standard to push it over the edge. It’s not trying to dislike it, it’s not even really disliking it or if it is it’s not a very strong one, I just feel like I do not see it at all.
snippet.textOriginal: Billie Eilish is the thing I get the least and I’m 23. snippet.textDisplay:
Controversial Opinion Incoming:

I don't like Bad Guy mostly because of the sounds chosen for this song.

Maybe it's just me, but Sunflower and Circles would be my pick considering they were most relaxing and peaceful for me. At times, I cried because the lyrics feel real for me combined with distinct sounds that doesn't sound like mainstream trap music or very bizarre.

It's a shame that Joji's Sanctuary isn't on the Billboards because the lyrics feels real for me added with unique sounds and a voice that sounds genuine (which is funny since he used to be a YouTuber playing his personas. That being PinkGuy and Filthy Frank) If it was then it will be my #1 song for me. Hopefully Joji will continue to make music in the 2020s...

snippet.textDisplay: i knew todd avoided talking about bts (bc part of the fandom is intense) but im glad that he finally accepted them and liked boy with luv, honestly bts music is so different each era and they explore a lot of genres too, i suggest to check songs like autumn leaves, home, save me, euphoria, cypher part 4 to name a few, also the boys themselves are really charismatic and down to earth, army can be a very intimidating fandom but if you respect the boys and dont mock their looks or nationalities we dont mind, the reason armys can get so aggressive is because we dont only have western fandoms talking sht abt them, but other kpop fandoms also join in the hate train and do the most “to ruin them” (yeah its sick i know) but overall what drew me to be a fan of bts is that they all have different and unique personalities and their albums have music with great messages that also makes you feel good.
